t two parameters define the size and queued packets limits of the input buffer, the last two of the output buffer.Buffer sizes are expressed in KiB, so {{Span|4 = 2^12 = 4096 bytes}}. All parameters will be rounded up to the nearest power of two.'''Note:''' HTML5 exports only use the input buffer since the output one is managed by browsers.